@sthursfield sorry for taking so long, but had other things to do... anyhow here's a small patch that fixes the insert of the blank node (this is against 2.1.6 release):

```
--- tracker-resource.c	2019-02-20 22:16:25.000000000 +0000
+++ tracker-2.1.8/src/libtracker-sparql/tracker-resource.c	2020-01-26 08:52:32.950381513 +0000
@@ -1019,7 +1019,7 @@
                                  GenerateTurtleData *data)
 {
 	/* We don't need to produce turtle for builtin classes */
-	if (is_builtin_class (tracker_resource_get_identifier (resource),
+	if (!is_blank_node(tracker_resource_get_identifier (resource)) && is_builtin_class (tracker_resource_get_identifier (resource),
 	                      data->all_namespaces))
 		return;

@@ -1317,7 +1317,7 @@
 		TrackerResource *relation = g_value_get_object (value);

 		/* We don't need to produce inserts for builtin classes */
-		if (is_builtin_class (tracker_resource_get_identifier (relation),
+		if (!is_blank_node(tracker_resource_get_identifier (relation)) && is_builtin_class (tracker_resource_get_identifier (relation),
 		                      data->namespaces))
 			return;
```

note, maybe it would be actually better do patch the `is_builtin_class`.... only thing that this doesn't take care of deleting the resource. i'm not so sure if i add a patch that actually deletes this node, would then the Resource RefCount take care of the fact in case 2 or more images has the very same GPS location?
